Yes, its possible, edit `data/users/content.json` file by:
```
...
  "permission_rules": {
   ".*": {
    "files_allowed": "data.json", 
    "max_size": 0
   }
  }, 
  "permissions": {
   "allowed1@zeroid.bit": { "max_size": 100000 },  
   "allowed2@zeroid.bit": { "max_size": 100000 },  
   "allowed3@zeroid.bit": { "max_size": 100000 },  
  }
...
```
then sign+publish this file using the sidebar

Restricting the view is harder, but can be possible: you need to encrypt the data files you want to hide and only share the key with the privileged users (ZeroMail works this way)

